age setting, where players with top\nfirst-stage efforts can proceed to the second stage competing for prizes. We\nestablish an intriguing negative result in this setting: there does not exist a\nsymmetric and monotone Perfect Bayesian equilibrium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 May 2022 05:59:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2023 01:06:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Apr 2023 17:36:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-20"}
